wikipedia_page.main: Sarah Inger Milne (born 17 January 1992) is an English badminton player from Leeds. In her junior career, she won the girls' doubles event at the 2009 English National Championships in the Under-17s and Under-19s event partnered with Jessica Fletcher. She also won the under-17s girls' singles and claimed silver medals in the under-17s mixed doubles and the under-19s girls' singles. At the European Junior Championships, she and Fletcher won the bronze medal in the girls' doubles event. In 2010, she represented Great Britain competed at the Summer Youth Olympics in Singapore. She lost her bronze medal match against the Vietnam's Vu Thi Trang in two games and finish fourth in the girls' singles event. In 2014, she announced her retirement from the badminton and withdrew herself from the GB programme.
